task.summary: Default task
Upload of code

Layout update: -Misc layout changes for spacing, size, etc. (modified div classes, cleaned up CSS) -CDUID text moved, no longer replaces page summary text on map update -Map given border, background colour, and new cursor to look more like an interactive element -Census divisions now highlight when selection -Census division outlines thinned and less fractured/pointy on zoom -Deeper zoom for smaller census divisions
Layout update: -Misc layout changes for a tile look (WIP)
-Minor style update -Fixed table number formats on map click/update
-Minor style update -Fixed table number formats on map click/update
-Fixed LMI rate number formats -Changed CSV headers for better page table titles
-Added search to selection process table -Added numbers to pie chart -General cleaning of code
-Changed numbers on pie to % share -Fixed pie number spacing, placement, transition

-Minor miscellaneous code cleanup -Changed make_pie call to match update_pie call (take data where CDUID = some number instead of whole csv file) -Moved code in pie_chart in preparation for smoothing visual transitions (ongoing)
-Fixed transitions on pie chart after first click on map
-Made introductory text dynamic (applications to advertisements for some CDUID)
-Changed text size on pie chart -Minor code cleanup
-Added colour series markers to commute time table To do: -Change header creation to be independent of CSV variable names
-Changed header assignment for LMI, commute, and occupation tables to be independent for CSV variables -Reset CSV variable names to original

-Code cleanup in tables.js -Removed 'update_table' in favour of modified 'make_table' as update was essentially destroying table rows and creating new ones. Changed associated function calls elsewhere.

-Added filter to datatable in footer -Changed original datatable call to match other calls and to allow for better filtering, performance on load To do: -Figure out how to move filter from footer to header while keeping column titles
-Moved selection process table filters to top of table. More testing is required. To do: -Remove filter for applications submitted or change it to a range filter.

-General updates to look and feel -Added "ALL" signifier to Selection process table filters -Shrank and thinned donut chart -Moved dynamic text & counters from page description paragraph to just below map -Removed image from page description
-Added Export and Print buttons to selection process table -To do: fix position of selection process table search box
-Removed selection process search box as filters make it unnecessary -Added tooltip text to pie chart slices on hover. For some CDUIDs, the slices are thin and regular text overlaps.
-Added tooltip text to map census divisions on hover. -Minor code cleanup
-Fixed selection process links on update -Minor code cleanup
-Added tooltip text to map census divisions on hover. -Minor code cleanup
-Re-activated search function so filters work properly
-Look and feel changes: -CD, advertisements, applications made larger and placed beside map -Made map larger -Map no longer jitters due to LMI table width change
-Minor look and feel changes -Removed filter for number of applications -Highlighted initial CD
-Minor look and feel changes -Removed filter for number of applications -Highlighted initial CD
-Made LMI indicators next to map into a clickable show/hide table -Made requisite style and alignment changes

-Position titles added to selection process CSV and table -Table formatting modified so width of titles doesn't force table out of container div -To fix: "max-width" setting for data table column seems to be more of a suggestion than actual formatting

Fixed issue: data table column width -Previous width setting for data table columns did not work as intended, seemed to be a chance of IntelliJ or browser cache -Drop-down filters were to blame: job posting titles are rarely uniform in formatting. -Set width using CSS -Removed drop-down for job titles. Search function is more useful.
Added normalized bar chart and table for education To do: -Make it update -Convert to D3 "slice" programming instead of using integer math for bar chart elements

Fixes and visual updates -Fixed bug in map where init CD is not "active" and colour sticks on change. -Edu table and bar chart now update -Bar chart text and borders removed -Added edu category on hover for bar chart elements
Visual tweaks -Updated hover on pie chart and bar chart to make it clearer -Changed bar chart colour scheme to colourblind-friendly ans cohesive scheme based on Brewer.
